'''花鱗魚屬'''（[[學名|屬名]]：{{lang|la|''Thelodus''}}，意為「乳頭般的小牙齒」<ref name = Agassiz1839>{{ cite book | author = Murchison, R. I. | chapter = Fishes and shells of the Ludlow and Wenlock Formations, or upper Silurian rocks | title = ''The Silurian System'' | publisher = [[約翰·默里公司|John Murray]] | year = 1839 | volume = 2 | pages = 605-633 | chapter-url = https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/165542#page/37/mode/1up }}</ref>{{rp|606}}）是[[無頜總綱|無頜魚類]]的一個[[屬|屬]]，屬於[[花鱗魚綱|花鱗魚綱]]的[[花鱗魚科|花鱗魚科]]<ref name = Burrow2013>{{ Cite journal | authors = Burrow, C. J.; Turner, S.; Nowlan, G. S.; Denison, R. H. | year = 2013 | title = Vertebrate Microremains from the Late Silurian of Arisaig, Nova Scotia, Canada | journal = ''Journal of Paleontology'' | volume = 87 | issue = 6 | issn = 0022-3360 | pages = 1041-1059 | doi = 10.1666/12-154 | url = https://www.researchgate.net/publication/258442501_Vertebrate_Microremains_from_the_Late_Silurian_of_Arisaig_Nova_Scotia_Canada }}</ref>，也是花鱗魚綱的[[模式屬|模式屬]]。花鱗魚屬包含多個物種，化石主要發現於[[北亞|北亞]]<ref name = Märss2002>{{ Cite journal | authors = Märss, T.; Karatajūtē-Talimaa, V. | year = 2002 | title = Ordovician and Lower Silurian thelodonts from Severnaya Zemlya Archipelago (Russia) | journal = ''Geodiversitas'' | volume = 24 | issue = 2 | issn = 1280-9659 | pages = 361-404 | doi = | url = https://www.researchgate.net/publication/242326812_Ordovician_and_Lower_Silurian_thelodonts_from_Severnaya_Zemlya_Archipelago_Russia }}</ref>、[[歐洲|歐洲]]<ref name = Agassiz1839/>與[[北美|北美]]<ref name = Burrow2013/>的[[志留紀|志留紀]]後期地層，在[[東亞|東亞]]也有可能的紀錄<ref name = Zhao2010>{{ Cite journal | authors = Zhao, W.-J.; Zhu, M. | year = 2010 | title = Siluro-Devonian vertebrate biostratigraphy and biogeography of China | journal = ''Palaeoworld'' | volume = 19 | issn = 1871-174X | pages = 4-26 | doi = 10.1016/j.palwor.2009.11.007 | url = http://www.ivpp.ac.cn/xwdt/kyjz/201811/P020181103476118829587.pdf }}</ref><ref name = Cui2020>{{ Cite journal | authors = Cui, X.-D.; Li, Q.; Qiao, T.; Zhu, M. | year = 2020 | title = New material of thelodonts from Lochkovian (Lower Devonian) of Qujing, Yunnan, China [云南曲靖下泥盆统洛霍考夫阶花鳞鱼类新材料] | journal = ''Vertebrata PalAsiatica'' | volume = 58 | issue = 1 | issn = 1000-9418 | pages = 1-15 | doi = 10.19615/j.cnki.1000-3118.190612 | url = https://www.researchgate.net/publication/333815231_New_material_of_thelodonts_from_Lochkovian_Lower_Devonian_of_Qujing_Yunnan_China }}</ref>。物種之間可能存在極大的體型差異，全長由4公分<ref name = Märss2011>{{ Cite journal | authors = Märss, T. | year = 2011 | title = A unique Late Silurian ''Thelodus'' squamation from Saaremaa (Estonia) and its ontogenetic development | journal = ''Estonian Journal of Earth Sciences'' | volume = 60 | issue = 3 | issn = 1736-4728 | pages = 137-146 | doi = 10.3176/earth.2011.3.02 | url = https://www.researchgate.net/publication/261090233_A_unique_Late_Silurian_Thelodus_squamation_from_Saaremaa_Estonia_and_its_ontogenetic_development }}</ref>至1公尺<ref name = Turner1986>{{ Cite journal | authors = Turner, S. | year = 2001 | title = Thelodus macintoshi Stetson 1928, the largest known thelodont (Agnatha : Thelodonti) | journal = ''Breviora'' | volume = 486 | issn = 0006-9698 | pages = 1-18 | doi = | url = https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/part/28067 }}</ref>不等。由化石埋藏環境推測，有些物種可能棲息於近岸海域<ref name = Turner1974>{{ Cite journal | authors = Turner, P.; Turner, S. | year = 1974 | title = Thelodonts from the upper Silurian of Ringerike, Norway | journal = ''Norsk Geologisk Tidsskrift'' | volume = 54 | issn = 0029-196X | pages = 183-192 | doi = | url = http://www.geologi.no/images/NJG_articles/NGT_54_2_183-192.pdf }}</ref>。

